sentences: Crowns were an English folk punk band from Launceston, Cornwall, England, formed in 2010.
The band consisted of lead singer and guitarist Bill Jefferson, bass player Jake Butler, mandolinist Jack Speckleton and drummer Rob Ramplin (replaced Nathan Haynes in 2013).
Formation (2010)
Crowns formed in 2010 after moving from Cornwall to London.
In July 2010, the band were invited to play a festival at the now defunct North London venue The Flowerpot, curated by the Communion record label.

In March 2012, Crowns released their first EP, Full Swing, featuring 6 tracks.
In January 2013, Crowns opened for The Dropkick Murphys at the London shows on their European tour.
Kissing Gates (2011)
On 22 September, Crowns announced the release of their debut single 'Kissing Gates' on their own imprint 'Ship Wreckords' and distributed by PIAS.
Released on 14 November 2011, the single was made available on limited edition 7" vinyl record and digital download.
In November 2011, Crowns were invited to support The King Blues on their UK tour alongside Cerebral Ballzy.
Stitches in the Flag (2012)
On 29 October 2012, Crowns released the single "Parting in the Porch", which is a song from their upcoming album, Stitches in the Flag.
Stitches in the Flag was released on 5 November 2012 and was positively received.
Split (2014)
Crowns played their final show in September 2014.
